Class DefaultValidator<C,E,D,G,L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.plugins.api.rest.resource.validation.Validator<C,E,D,G,L>
      • com.communote.plugins.api.rest.resource.validation.DefaultValidator<C,E,D,G,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - create resource parameter
    E - edit resource parameter
    D - delete resource parameter
    G - get resource parameter
    L - list resource parameter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    UserResourceValidator

    public class DefaultValidator<C,E,D,G,L>
extends Validator<C,E,D,G,L>
    Default implementation of the validator. It is used, if no others are specified. By default all validations are passed. A concrete validator can inherit from this class. In this case only the relevant methods should be overridden.
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/
